$interpreted: Soohyeon: Yonghyeon...
Yonghyeon: The peach tree is young and brilliant, our young lady sets off to her new house and home...
Yonghyeon: ...I offer my congratulations to you both.
Soohyeon: ...Thank you, Yonghyeon.
Juan-Yun: Don't worry, Yonghyeon. I will take good care of Soohyeon.
Juan-Yun: You're her best friend. I won't let you down.
Yonghyeon: I trust that you won't.
Seahorse Competitor: Why'd they have to get married during the tournament!? What a pain...
Wolf Competitor: I heard it was supposed to be after the tournament, but those damn diplomats messed with the timing.
Seahorse Competitor: Then why couldn't they just push back the marriage as well?
Wolf Competitor: The fortune teller told them this was the best time. It'd be bad luck to wait.
Seahorse Competitor: You know this really grinds my gears.
Seahorse Competitor: It's enough that I've got to respect him even though he can't walk and he's at the beck and call of that maggot princess.
Seahorse Competitor: But now he's got to go ahead and take our Soohyeon too!?
Seahorse Competitor: This is getting out of hand!
Wolf Competitor: What? You want to teach him a lesson?
Toyokuni: I didn't think you'd come.
Tindoiimu: ...Are you talking to me?
Toyokuni: You're the only one here.
Toyokuni: Himawari got a headache, she went to take a rest.
Toyokuni: I think it was just an excuse to leave. You know how she feels about Juan-Yun...
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: ...I didn't think I'd come, either.
Tindoiimu: But since she invited humans and fugitives, too, I figured why not...
Toyokuni: Why not indeed. Soohyeon has always been a friend to you, anyhow.
Toyokuni: But... I thought you and Juan-Yun...
Tindoiimu: I've known they were to be wed for a long time now. There's nothing between Juan-Yun and me.
Toyokuni: ......
Toyokuni: ...Alright. I won't press further, then.
Tindoiimu: (That's right... I've always known they'd get married... Then, why do I still feel...)
Wolf Competitor: Come on! If you don't drink it, you're disrespecting our sect!
Juan-Yun: I don't mean any disrespect! It's just...
Seahorse Competitor: Every guest spits some wine into a cup, and then the groom has to drink it up. It's Water Sect tradition!
Seahorse Competitor: What, you scared of a little booze? I didn't realize that accident you had as a kid made you scared of all liquid.
Wolf Competitor: It's not that hard, little lord. Drink or no drink?
Soohyeon: Excuse me!? That 'tradition' is only used to haze grooms that nobody likes. How dare you do this to Juan-Yun!?
Seahorse Competitor: Soohyeon, we're doing this for you! Don't get in the way!
Soohyeon: This has nothing to do with...
Yonghyeon: Soohyeon's right. You're just tormenting him.
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon!
Seahorse Competitor: Stand aside, newt-boy! Why don't you go blend into a wall somewhere?
Yonghyeon: If you're sticking to tradition, then if the groom doesn't want to drink it, he can challenge the guests to a duel.
Yonghyeon: If the groom wins, then the guests have to drink it instead. I know you don't like us salamanders, but we're Water Sect, too. We know the rules.
Yonghyeon: And I'm not gonna stand around and watch you bully Soohyeon's husband, so I'm fighting with him!
Seahorse Competitor: You little...
Juan-Yun: Hey, today is a day for celebration. Can't we all just get along?
Wolf Competitor: Fine, you wanna fight, let's fight! We're in the damn tournament, you think we're scared of some frog-boy and the wheelchair-wonder over here?
Yonghyeon: What'd you just say!?
Yonghyeon: I'm gonna bust you up toothless and make you say it again!
Soohyeon: I'll help the both of you fight, too.
Seahorse Competitor: Hold on... not you, Soohyeon! You're too strong... and you're the arbiter's daughter...
Soohyeon: Too late!
Juan-Yun: Alright, It's a special day for me, so I'll let you off easy. And I think you've both learned your lesson, right?
Wolf Competitor: Yeah~ We were just jokin' around~
Wolf Competitor: Come on, let's all have a drink!
Seahorse Competitor: Yaaaaagh—!! The floor's all slippery, I can't stop!!
Soohyeon: Juan-Yun!
Seahorse Competitor: Sorry~ I'm not that good of a swimmer, I could only save myself! What should we do!?
Yonghyeon: Shut up, you did that on purpose! You know he's afraid of water!
Tindoiimu: (Juan-Yun! Wake up! Juan-Yun!!)
Juan-Yun: ......
Tindoiimu: (Juan-Yun! You've got to wake up! You'll die!!)
Juan-Yun: ......
Tindoiimu: (You can't die, you can't die... I won't let you die!)
